      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Three damage suits against the\nNorthern Pacific railroad were filed\nwith the clerk of the United States\ndistrict court today, being removed\nfrom the superior court.\n\n\nSarah May Wright puts a valuation\nof $4,000 on her husbands life. He\nwss killed by a train at Gem, Idaho,\nlast November. The complainant al\nleges that the railroad run its trains\nthrough the main street of Gem and\ndo not put up proper lights to warn\npeople.\n\n\nBeatrice NJ. Smith wants $4,000"
    }
